data.name: lblCost.ToolTip
data.value:
The total price is based off the number of documents, DPI, and color mode.
Here are some proportions: -The higher the page count, the lower the price per page. -The higher the DPI, the higher the count. -Color scans are more expensive.

data.name: cboDPI.ToolTip
data.value:
DPI is an acronym for Dots Per Inch. Essentially, it determines the resolution of the files, which determines the clarity of the document.
Logically, higher DPI batches are more expensive than lower ones.
